<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6a5683c-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s30909"><num value="30909">§ 30909.</num><heading> Security</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Neither the United States nor a federally-owned corporation may be required to give a bond or admiralty stipulation in a civil action under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6a5683d-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s6/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 6(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1519">120 Stat. 1519</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
